     LLLLOOOOOOOOKKKK((((UUUU1111))))             LLLLSSSS----DDDDOOOOSSSS 6666 ---- UUUUttttiiiilllliiiittttiiiieeeessss 1111              LLLLOOOOOOOOKKKK((((UUUU1111))))



          ----mmmm or ----pppp
               This option routes the output of _l_o_o_k through the
               _m_o_r_e(U1) utility.  The screen will pause once 23 lines
               of text have been displayed.  The _m_o_r_e(U1) prompt
               ("--More--") allows you to advance or search through
               the remainder of the display.  See the _m_o_r_e(U1) command
               for information on the options that _m_o_r_e(U1) provides.
               The ----pppp and ----mmmm options are ignored if the output is
               redirected.

          ----qqqq   The headers and other general information are not
               displayed.

          ----tttt   The summary on the media type and its organization is
               displayed but no allocation map is produced.  This
               command is the opposite of ----aaaa and only works on LS-DOS,
               LDOS and TRSDOS 6 disks.

          ----uuuu   Cylinders that are completely unassigned are not
               displayed in the allocation map.  This option is
               ignored if ----ffff or ----cccc are used.  This command only works
               on LS-DOS, LDOS and TRSDOS 6 disks.

          ----!!!!   Causes _l_o_o_k to ignore any default settings that are
               specified in the DDDDEEEEFFFFAAAAUUUULLLLTTTTSSSS////MMMMAAAADDDD file.  _L_o_o_k will also
               ignore any options that are specified to the left of
               the ----!!!! option.  Note that the DDDDEEEEFFFFAAAAUUUULLLLTTTTSSSS////MMMMAAAADDDD file is
               accessed even if the ----!!!! option is specified.

          ----???? oooorrrr ----hhhh
               Displays the help message.

          [:]_d_r_i_v_e
               Specifies the logical drive that contains the disk to
               analyze.  The logical drive number can be a diskette,
               hard disk, or _D_i_s_k_D_i_s_k(M).  A drive number must be
               specified unless the ----ffff option is used.

          ----ffff _f_i_l_e_n_a_m_e::::_d_r_i_v_e
               Locates the granules that the specified file occupies.
               This command only works on LS-DOS, LDOS and TRSDOS 6
               disks.  The _d_r_i_v_e number must be specified.

          ----cccc _c_y_l_i_n_d_e_r
               By specifying a particular _c_y_l_i_n_d_e_r and a _s_e_c_t_o_r or a
               _g_r_a_n_u_l_e, _l_o_o_k will determine which file is assigned to
               that location on the disk.  The _c_y_l_i_n_d_e_r number can be
               specified in decimal, or in hexadecimal by preceding
               the number with 0000xxxx, such as 0x14.

               When ----cccc is specified, ----gggg or ----ssss must also be specified.
               The ----cccc option cannot be used with the ----ffff option.



