     LLLLOOOOOOOOKKKK((((UUUU1111))))             LLLLSSSS----DDDDOOOOSSSS 6666 ---- UUUUttttiiiilllliiiittttiiiieeeessss 1111              LLLLOOOOOOOOKKKK((((UUUU1111))))



          _L_o_o_k uses the LLLLOOOOOOOOKKKK////IIIINNNNIIII file to identify disks made by
          operating systems other than LS-DOS, LDOS or TRSDOS 6.  The
          LLLLOOOOOOOOKKKK////IIIINNNNIIII file contains ssssiiiiggggnnnnaaaattttuuuurrrreeeessss that are compared against
          the diskette being tested.  When a match is made, the
          description from the LLLLOOOOOOOOKKKK////IIIINNNNIIII file is displayed.

          The LLLLOOOOOOOOKKKK////IIIINNNNIIII file that is included with _l_o_o_k(U1) contains
          signatures so that _l_o_o_k can recognize these alien formats:
                TRSDOS 1.1, 1.3, 2.3, 2.7DD   NEWDOS 2.0, 2.5
                MULTIDOS 1.6, 1.7             MS/PC-DOS (low cap)
                MODEL 100/200                 Various CP/M formats
                Color Computer                Datasoft

          Additional entries can be added to the LLLLOOOOOOOOKKKK////IIIINNNNIIII file so that
          more formats can be recognized.  This file can be modified
          with almost any editor.

          Each entry in LLLLOOOOOOOOKKKK////IIIINNNNIIII starts at the beginning of a line and
          has the following format:

                sssseeeeccccttttoooorrrr ssssiiiizzzzeeee,,,, ccccyyyylllliiiinnnnddddeeeerrrr,,,, sssseeeeccccttttoooorrrr,,,, ooooffffffffsssseeeetttt,,,, ccccoooouuuunnnntttt
                ppppaaaatttttttteeeerrrrnnnn  """"ssssttttrrrriiiinnnngggg""""

          Here is an example of an entry in the LLLLOOOOOOOOKKKK////IIIINNNNIIII file:
                1,0,1,0,6  0x01,0x00,0x00,0x4e,0x58,0x5a  "TRSDOS 2.3"
          Each parameter is described below.

          The sssseeeeccccttttoooorrrr ssssiiiizzzzeeee is a number and must be one of the
          following:
                0     for 128 byte sectors (3740 format)
                1     for 256 byte sectors (most Model III/4 formats)
                2     for 512 byte sectors (some CP/M and all MS-DOS
                      formats)
                3     for 1024 byte sectors (no known examples)

          The ccccyyyylllliiiinnnnddddeeeerrrr field specifies which cylinder is to be
          examined to test for this format.  The ccccyyyylllliiiinnnnddddeeeerrrr number is a
          value from 00 to 79.  You should avoid using a cylinder
          above 39 as part of your signature as these locations cannot
          be reached on a 40 cylinder drive, and could damage the
          drive.

          The sssseeeeccccttttoooorrrr field specifies which sector is to be read to
          test for this format.  Note that _l_o_o_k will run faster if you
          keep all the entries that specify the same sssseeeeccccttttoooorrrr ssssiiiizzzzeeee,
          ccccyyyylllliiiinnnnddddeeeerrrr and sssseeeeccccttttoooorrrr number together.  The sector will only
          have to be read from the diskette a single time if you do
          this.







